    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-02-11T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-02-11T07:00:00-05:00" n="681"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d681">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">693.002/505: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-02-11T20:00:00+08:00"
                            >February 11, 1938—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received February 11—6:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>244. Reference your 129, February 9, 8 p.m.<note n="59" xml:id="d681fn59">This
                        telegram repeated the Department’s No. 51, February 9, 8 p.m., to the
                        Ambassador in Japan, <ref target="#pg_650">p. 650</ref>.</note> Hall-Patch,
                    Financial Adviser, British Embassy, told me yesterday afternoon he has definite
                    information from officer of Japanese Consulate General with whom he discussed
                    matter several days ago that the Japanese have <pb facs="0658" n="654"
                        xml:id="pg_654"/> intention of decreasing Shanghai quotas for foreign loan
                    and indemnity services <hi rend="italic">pari passu</hi> with decrease in
                    revenue. I had received no such intimation from the Japanese or from the
                    customs.</p>
                <p>The essence of the press interview given by Matsui is correctly stated in your
                    message. I am telegraphing separately full text.<note n="60" xml:id="d681fn60"
                        >Telegram No. 245, February 11, 9 p.m., not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>I have no information on other points mentioned.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Tokyo.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gauss</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
